\displaystyle\lim_{n \to \infty} n \ln\left(1+\frac{1}{n}\right)=1
x-\frac{1}{2}x^2+ \frac{1}{3}x^3 ...
x = 1/n \implies \ln (1 + 1/n) = 1/n - \frac{1}{2}(\frac{1}{n})^2 + \frac{1}{3}(\frac{1}{n})^3 + \cdots \implies n\ln(1 + 1/n) = 1 - \frac{1}{2}(\frac{1}{n}) + \frac{1}{3}(\frac{1}{n})^2 + \cdots = 1 + O(\frac{1}{n})
\lim\limits_{n\to \infty} n\ln (1 + 1/n) = 1
